[recto] Ad [Addendum] 61. BM Print Room. Bruegel. Popham 9. A Fool trying to hold an emthy (??) [sic] Egg. In the sam edirection and copy from Twelve Flemish Provrebs, othe rcopies corresponding with engraving (Bastelaer drawing 101), though near to B. in style. To feeble and hesitating for B. himself. Yes!; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. especially right sleeve and head; [verso] the arm resting on the egg cf. a connoisseur in Albertina drawing i.e. the design is similar, not the execution!'
